BP Southern Africa has announced that it will be donating R8 million to help support relief efforts in KwaZulu-Natal following the devastating floods. This will be done through the company’s ongoing partnership with the Solidarity Fund. According to the company’s CEO, Taelo Mojapelo, the donation will provide displaced flood victims with food, water, and other essential emergency supplies. “The health, safety and security of our people and our environment are core BP values and we are pleased to be able to provide meaningful and critical support towards the country’s collective stand to help those in need in the province,” said Mojapelo. ALSO READ | KZN Floods: Pietermaritzburg organisations assist victims Mojalepo thanked board chairperson, advocate Thandi Orleyn, for making the donation possible, adding that they will continue to support their colleagues and impacted retail sites. He added that they are pleased to support the communities where their employees live and work.